Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Trim the @courgette{1}, then halve lengthways. Slice widthways into 2cm thick pieces.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(peeled and halved). Slice each half into 4 wedges. Peel and thinly slice the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Drain the @halloumi{250%g}, then cut into slices (3 per person). Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Pop the potatoes and onion onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%tsp}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the aubergine, courgette and garlic onto another baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper then toss to coat.

After ~{5%minutes} of roasting time, pop the courgette and aubergine tray onto the middle shelf of the oven and roast until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When the veg has 10 mins of roasting time left, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the tray and cook for the remaining time until golden.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

While the veg is roasting, pop the @fresh pesto{32%g} into a small bowl and add the @water{1%tbsp}.

Mix it together - it should be drizzling consistency.

> TIP: Add more water if you'd prefer it more drizzly.

When 5 mins of roasting time remain, remove the halloumi slices from the cold water. Pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

When everything is ready, share the potatoes and vegetables between your plates.

Lay the halloumi slices on top and finish by drizzling the pesto all over.

Enjoy!